Parser_schema:
The output should be formatted as a JSON instance that conforms to the JSON schema below.

As an example, for the schema {"properties": {"foo": {"title": "Foo", "description": "a list of strings", "type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}}}, "required": ["foo"]}
the object {"foo": ["bar", "baz"]} is a well-formatted instance of the schema. The object {"properties": {"foo": ["bar", "baz"]}} is not well-formatted.

Here is the output schema:
```
{"$defs": {"ChessMove": {"properties": {"move": {"description": "Coup d'échec au format case de départ case de fin.", "title": "Move", "type": "string"}, "explanation": {"description": "Explication complète du mouvement, y compris le raisonnement stratégique, les considérations tactiques et les résultats potentiels.", "title": "Explanation", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["move", "explanation"], "title": "ChessMove", "type": "object"}}, "properties": {"candidate_moves": {"description": "List of 5 legal candidate moves to play this turn, chosen from the list. Each move should be presented in the format start square end square (e.g., e2e4) without using dashes, along with a detailed explanation.", "items": {"$ref": "#/$defs/ChessMove"}, "title": "Candidate Moves", "type": "array"}, "best_move": {"description": "Coup à jouer au format uci", "items": {"$ref": "#/$defs/ChessMove"}, "title": "Best Move", "type": "array"}}, "required": ["candidate_moves", "best_move"]}
```
